{"lemma":"تَبْدِيلٌ","slug":"تَبْدِيلٌ","root":"ب.د.ل","root_slug":"ب-د-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-د-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"تَبْدِيل","root":"بدل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":7},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2003"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%AF%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%84%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَدَّلَ (baddala) (form II)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"giving in exchange, exchange"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alteration, modification"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"conversion"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of بَدَّلَ (baddala)."},"ipa":["/tab.diːl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2003","headword_ar":"تَبْدِيلٌ","root":"bdl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"properly signifies [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"changing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altering,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing; or] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"changing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altering, the form,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fashion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"semblance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the quality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of a thing,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to another form,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"while the substance remains the same;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, T, TA;) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"changing"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from its state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Arafeh, TA;) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"changing"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without substitution:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) but the Arabs have used it also in the sense of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibodaAlN","text_ar":"اـِبْدَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mbr, T, TA,) which signifies [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"changing"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by substitution; exchanging"},{"kind":"text","text":"it;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"replacing"},{"kind":"text","text":"it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with another thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"removing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"displacing, the substance"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of a thing],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and introducing anew another substance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, T, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bad~alotuhu","text_ar":"بَدَّلْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabodiylN","text_ar":"تَبْدِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, * Msb, K,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I changed it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altered it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I changed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altered, the form,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fashion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"semblance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the quality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition, of it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) as in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bad~alotu AlxaAtama biAlHaloqapi","text_ar":"بَدَّلْتُ الخَاتَمَ بِالحَلْقَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I changed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altered, the signet-ring into the simple ring"},{"kind":"text","text":"], said when one has melted the former and made of it a simple ring; (Fr, T, TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bad~ala A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"بَدَّلَ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ayiy^~aAti HasanaAtK","text_ar":"السَّيِيَّاتِ حَسَنَاتٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God changed the evil deeds into good deeds"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; the verb being doubly trans. by itself because it has the meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEala","text_ar":"جَعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Say~ara","text_ar":"صَيَّرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb. [But see what follows.]) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abodalotuhu","text_ar":"اَبْدَلْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bika*aA","text_ar":"بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in the S,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abodalotu Al$~aYo'a bigayorihi","text_ar":"اَبْدَلْتُ الشَّىْءَ بِغَيْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without explanation,] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibodaAlN","text_ar":"اـِبْدَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I changed it by substituting for it such a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exchanged it for such a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"replaced it with such a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said when one has removed the first, and put the second in its place; (Msb;) as in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abodalotu AlxaAtama biAlHaloqapi","text_ar":"اَبْدَلْتُ الخَاتَمَ بِالحَلْقَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I changed the signet-ring by substituting for it the simple ring; exchanged the signet-ring for the simple ring;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"replaced the signet-ring with the simple ring"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; said when one removes the one, and puts the other in its place: (Fr, T, TA:) and this verb is also made doubly trans. by itself, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bad~alotu","text_ar":"بَدَّلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) which is used in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abodalotu","text_ar":"اَبْدَلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as shown above]; (Mbr, T, TA;) for instance, where it is said, [in the Kur lxvi. 5,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EasaY rab~uhu A_ino Tal~aqakun~a A^ano yubodilahu","text_ar":"عَسَى رَبُّهُ اـِنْ طَلَّقَكُنَّ اَنْ يُبْدِلَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azowajFA xayorFA minokun~a","text_ar":"اَزْوَجًا خَيْرًا مِنْكُنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May-be, his Lord, if he divorce you, will give him in exchange wives better than you"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; accord to one reading,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yubad~ilahu","text_ar":"يُبَدِّلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) An ex. of the latter of these two verbs in the sense of the former is the saying in the Kur [xxv. 70],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yubad~ilu A@ll~`hu say~iA=tihimo HasanaAtK","text_ar":"يُبَدِّلُ ا@للّٰهُ سَيِّا=تِهِمْ حَسَنَاتٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God will change their evil deeds by substituting for them good deeds"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; i. e. will cancel the evil deeds and put in their place good deeds: but in the saying in the Kur [iv. 59],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~amaA naDijato juluwduhumo bad~alonaAhumo juluwdFA","text_ar":"كُلَّمَا نَضِجَتْ جُلُودُهُمْ بَدَّلْنَاهُمْ جُلُودًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayorahaA","text_ar":"غَيْرَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whenever their skins are thoroughly burned, we will change the condition thereof to them into the condition of other skins"},{"kind":"text","text":"], the meaning is, that the first condition of their skins shall be restored;"},{"kind":"page_break","n":168},{"kind":"text","text":"so that the substance is one, but the condition is different. (Mbr, T, TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bad~alahu A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"بَدَّلَهُ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mana Alxawofi A^amonFA","text_ar":"مَنَ الخَوْفِ اَمْنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God gave him in exchange for fear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in lieu of fear, security"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bad~alahu bihi ka*aA","text_ar":"بَدَّلَهُ بِهِ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave him in exchange for it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in lieu of it, such a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see Kur xxxiv. 15. And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bd~l makaAnahu ka*aA","text_ar":"بدّل مَكَانَهُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave in exchange for it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in lieu of it, such a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see Kur vii. 93 and xvi. 103.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bad~ala HusonFA baEoda suwo'K","text_ar":"بَدَّلَ حُسْنًا بَعْدَ سُوْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xxvii. 11], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hath done good [by way of exchange after evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repented;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bad~ala *anobuhu biAltawobapi","text_ar":"بَدَّلَ ذَنْبُهُ بِالتَوْبَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hath exchanged his sin for repentance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Bd.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabodiylN","text_ar":"تَبْدِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibodaAlN","text_ar":"اـِبْدَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"both signify The act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exchanging"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a thing for another thing]; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a thing]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be a substitute"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for another thing]; (KL, PS;) and so does ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badaAlN","text_ar":"بَدَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (KL.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bd~l Al$~aYo'a mina Al$aYo'i","text_ar":"بدّل الشَّىْءَ مِنَ الشَىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K, *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minohu","text_ar":"مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abdlhu","text_ar":"ابدلهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~axa*ahu minohu badlFA","text_ar":"اِتَّخَذَهُ مِنْهُ بَدلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He exchanged the thing for the thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, more literally,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made the thing a substitute for the thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, K. [In the text of the former of these, as given in the TT, instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~axa*ahu","text_ar":"اِتَّخَذَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", I find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taxi*a","text_ar":"تَخِذَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~axa*a","text_ar":"اِتَّخَذَ"},{"kind":"text","text":") without the affixed pronoun, which is meant to be understood or is omitted inadvertently by the transcriber: and here it should be observed, that the explanation which I have rendered as above admits of another meaning, namely,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*ahu minohu badalFA","text_ar":"اَخَذَهُ مِنْهُ بَدَلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"“he took it as a substitute for it:” in the M, immediately before,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*ahu minohu badalFA","text_ar":"اَخَذَهُ مِنْهُ بَدَلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is given as the explanation of the phrases"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tbd~l Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"تبدّل الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAl$~aYo'i","text_ar":"بِالشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astbdlhu","text_ar":"استبدلهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 10.]) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~awoba bigayorihi","text_ar":"الثَّوْبَ بِغَيْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badalotu","text_ar":"بَدَلْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", [inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badaAlN","text_ar":"بَدَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned and explained above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I exchanged the garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth, for another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made it to be a substitute for another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisotabodalotuhu","text_ar":"اِسْتَبْدَلْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bigayorihi","text_ar":"بِغَيْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (Msb. [But the latter phrase has more frequently another meaning, explained below: see 10.]) [↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abdlhu","text_ar":"ابدلهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the phrases"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abdlhu ka*aA","text_ar":"ابدلهُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He changed it into,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"substituted for it, such a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abdlhu mino ka*aA","text_ar":"ابدلهُ مِنْ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he changed it from,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"substituted it for, such a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is more common than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bd~lh","text_ar":"بدّله"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is used in the same sense; as ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badalahu","text_ar":"بَدَلَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also; for] AO applies the term ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maboduwlN","text_ar":"مَبْدُولٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in lieu of the more common term ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mubodalN","text_ar":"مُبْدَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"] to a letter that is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"changed"},{"kind":"text","text":"from another letter, as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madahotuhu","text_ar":"مَدَهْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madaHotuhu","text_ar":"مَدَحْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and this shows that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badalotu","text_ar":"بَدَلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is trans. [and signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I changed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (Az, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mbr","T","TA","M","K","Fr","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}